# Testing and Debugging

## Test Environment

All tests use `TempDir` for isolation. `KnowledgeGraph::new(temp_dir.path())` creates
`<temp_dir>/knowledge.db` automatically. No `env.sh`, no model downloads, no server needed.

---

## Running Tests

```bash
cargo test --workspace -- --test-threads=1                             # All tests — always single-threaded
cargo test --workspace storage -- --test-threads=1                     # Module-specific
cargo test --workspace -- --test-threads=1 --nocapture                 # With stdout
RUST_LOG=debug cargo test --workspace -- --test-threads=1 --nocapture  # With debug logging
cargo test --workspace test_name -- --exact --test-threads=1           # Single test by name
```

Always pass `--test-threads=1`. Integration tests share GPU/NPU hardware on a live
Lemonade Server and fail intermittently when run in parallel. Unit tests pass with
no external service. Integration tests skip automatically when no server is reachable.

