## Transcription Providers in Tests

### Mock transcription provider (no server required)

For tests that need a `TranscriptionProvider` without a live server, implement
the trait inline:

```rust
use u_forge_core::ai::transcription::TranscriptionProvider;

struct MockTranscriptionProvider;

#[async_trait::async_trait]
impl TranscriptionProvider for MockTranscriptionProvider {
    async fn transcribe(
        &self,
        _audio_bytes: Vec<u8>,
        filename: &str,
    ) -> anyhow::Result<String> {
        Ok(format!("mock transcript for {}", filename))
    }

    fn model_name(&self) -> &str {
        "mock-whisper"
    }
}
```

### WAV test helper: `make_silence_wav`

`make_silence_wav(duration_secs: f32) -> Vec<u8>` lives in the `ai::transcription::tests`
module (`src/ai/transcription.rs`). It builds a valid mono 16-bit 16 kHz PCM WAV entirely
in memory — no binary fixtures needed. Refer to the source for the implementation; copy the
pattern when you need real audio bytes in a test.

> **`LemonadeTranscriptionProvider::new` is synchronous** — no probe at construction.
> Errors surface only when `transcribe()` is called. There is no `TranscriptionManager`.

Transcription integration tests use the same `require_integration_url!()` macro
as all other integration tests. See `src/test_helpers.rs` for the implementation.

